<p class="">Of course he did, in his statement the other day to the House. This is the fifth time that this ratio has been changed, and we cannot help gradu- <span id="1674" class="column-number" data-column-number="1674"></span> ally coming to the conclusion that the fixing of the ratio has more to do with the right hon. Gentleman's state of digestion than with any statistical estimate of needs. Experience has shown that it is quite impossible to fix for the whole country a ratio which has any meaning at all. The Minister in his announcement the other day—and we are glad of it—said that he would allow more flexibility in the application of this new ratio.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
